LGBTQI-plus advocacy lead for the organisation Civicus, Mawethu Nkosana spoke with eNCA's Sally Burdett. Courtesy of #DStv403 LUANDA - Angola has officially enacted a 2019 law decriminalising homosexuality. It prohibits discrimination based upon a person’s sexual orientation. READ: Escaping the 'bubble': LGBT tourism eyes new horizons Civicus's Mawethu Nkosana says this will help the fight against LGBTI discrimination. Watch the full interview in the video above.